{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d804de4f-a78e-487f-91ed-8e088692eb53","content":"Yes, both APIs are valid in .NET MAUI on .NET 10, but here are the details:\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Correct. This is an iOS platform-specific property that automatically adds padding so content doesn't overlap the notch/Dynamic Island. You need the namespace:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\nThen apply it:\n```xml\n<ContentPage ... ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Also correct. Set this on a layout (like `Grid`) to let it extend *into* the safe area, which is exactly what you want for a full-bleed background image while the rest of your content stays safe.\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\n**Typical pattern** — combine both: enable `UseSafeArea` on the page for general content safety, then use `IgnoreSafeArea` on a specific inner layout that holds the background image. This gives you edge-to-edge visuals with properly inset interactive content.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"26db4279-aad0-426e-8d17-5f11c5bd0c3f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid for background images\n\nLet me think about what I know about .NET MAUI safe area APIs, and whether these are correct for .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the safe area handling for iOS has evolved. Let me search for any relevant information in the repository since there might be skill plugins or documentation about this.\n\nActually, the user is asking a general .NET MAUI question - not about code in this repository. \n\nFrom my knowledge, `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` is indeed a valid platform-specific property from the Xamarin.Forms era that carries into .NET MAUI, requiring the appropriate iOS-specific namespace to be declared. The `IgnoreSafeArea` property exists in .NET MAUI as well, though I should verify the exact implementation details and whether these are the current recommended approaches for handling safe areas in .NET 10. preview. Both `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` and `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` should remain valid in .NET 10 — the former is the iOS platform-specific API that adjusts page padding for safe areas, while the latter allows content to extend beyond those boundaries on layout views.","outputTokens":1062,"requestId":"1017:BAEFE:ACB20CC:BB85224:69FD37FA"},"id":"b7a321a3-0f7d-484a-bed5-812d8e346814","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:10:40.253Z","parentId":"4d9873e6-3d85-43f8-9bd8-d9303e5eaf72"}
